.TH REKAP 1 "November 2025" "rekap 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rekap \- Daily Mac Activity Summary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rekap
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
[\fICOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rekap
is a single-binary macOS CLI application that provides a daily activity summary with a friendly, animated terminal UI. It analyzes today's computer activity including uptime, battery usage, app usage, screen time, browser activity, network activity, and notifications.
.PP
rekap is privacy-first: no historical database, no cloud sync, no telemetry. All data stays local on your Mac and only today's activity is analyzed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-accessible
Enable accessibility mode (color-blind friendly, high contrast)
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Output machine-parsable key=value format for scripting
.TP
.BR \-\-theme " " \fITHEME\fR
Use a color theme. Built-in themes: default, minimal, hacker, pastel, nord, dracula, solarized. Can also specify a path to a custom theme file.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B rekap
Display today's activity summary with all available data
.TP
.B rekap completion \fISHELL\fR
Generate shell completion script for bash, zsh, or fish
.TP
.B rekap demo
Display sample output with randomized fake data to preview the format
.TP
.BR "rekap demo \-\-theme " \fITHEME\fR
Preview a color theme using demo data
.TP
.B rekap doctor
Check capabilities and permissions status. Shows which macOS permissions are granted and what features are available.
.TP
.B rekap init
Run the guided permission setup wizard to enable Full Disk Access and other permissions
.SH FEATURES
.B rekap
provides the following information about today's computer activity:
.TP
.B System
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Uptime and awake time tracking
.IP \(bu 2
Battery usage monitoring (start/current percentage, plug events)
.IP \(bu 2
Screen lock events and break patterns
.RE
.TP
.B Productivity
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Top apps by usage time (up to 3 apps displayed)
.IP \(bu 2
Screen-on time calculation
.IP \(bu 2
Focus streak detection (longest continuous time in one app)
.IP \(bu 2
Context fragmentation score (measures task-switching)
.RE
.TP
.B Browser Activity
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Open tabs count per browser (Chrome, Safari, Edge)
.IP \(bu 2
Browser history analysis (today's URLs only)
.IP \(bu 2
Most-visited domains
.IP \(bu 2
Issue/ticket URL detection (Jira, GitHub, Linear, GitLab, Azure DevOps, etc.)
.IP \(bu 2
Domain categorization (work vs distraction vs neutral)
.RE
.TP
.B Network Activity
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Active network interface and name
.IP \(bu 2
Data transferred (bytes received/sent)
.RE
.TP
.B Notifications
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Total notification count
.IP \(bu 2
Top interrupting apps
.RE
.TP
.B Now Playing
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Currently playing media track and app (optional)
.RE
.TP
.B Wellness Check
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Burnout warnings for long days, excessive task-switching, tab overload
.IP \(bu 2
Screen time alerts
.RE
.SH PERMISSIONS
.B rekap
works without any permissions but provides enhanced data when granted:
.TP
.B Full Disk Access
Required for: App usage tracking, screen time data, focus streaks, notification tracking
.TP
.B Accessibility
Required for: Frontmost app detection (fallback method)
.TP
.B Media/Now Playing
Required for: Track currently playing media
.PP
To set up permissions, run:
.B rekap init
.PP
To check current permission status, run:
.B rekap doctor
.SH CONFIGURATION
.B rekap
supports a configuration file at:
.PP
.RS
.B ~/.config/rekap/config.yaml
.RE
.PP
Available configuration options:
.TP
.B Color Scheme
Customize primary, secondary, accent, and text colors
.TP
.B Display Preferences
Show/hide specific sections (battery, media, etc.)
.TP
.B Time Format
Choose between 12-hour or 24-hour format
