.SH PRIVACY
All data stays on your Mac. rekap does not:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Store historical data
.IP \(bu 2
Sync to the cloud
.IP \(bu 2
Send telemetry
.IP \(bu 2
Track you across days
.RE
.PP
Only today's activity is analyzed, and all analysis happens locally on your device.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Operating System
macOS 11.0 (Big Sur) or later
.TP
.B Permissions (Optional)
Full Disk Access, Accessibility, Media/Now Playing
.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.TP
.B "Screen Time unavailable" message
Run
.B rekap init
to set up Full Disk Access. Grant permission to your terminal app in System Settings → Privacy & Security → Full Disk Access.
.TP
.B No app data showing
Ensure Full Disk Access is granted (check with
.B rekap doctor
). Restart your terminal after granting permissions. Verify that macOS Screen Time is enabled in System Settings → Screen Time.
.TP
.B Binary won't run (Gatekeeper)
On first run, right-click the binary and select "Open" to bypass Gatekeeper, or run:
.RS
.nf
xattr -d com.apple.quarantine /usr/local/bin/rekap
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B Check permissions status
Run
.B rekap doctor
to see current permission status and available features.
